I am not a born entrepreneur. What I am is relentless. At first I was relentless about making money which burned me out. Now, I am relentless about chasing FULFILLMENT, and it’s this pursuit, the dogged determination of finding and satiating my need to live a life worth living, that drives me every day. In shifting my focus I have been able to build massively successful companies, avoid burn out, and truly live! But it took me YEARS, no fucking joke, YEARS to get here. 

If you are looking to find fulfillment and get real results in your business I want to invite you to join my Business Decision Making Workshop. This is a 4-week intensive for anyone with a 6-figure+ business looking to take things to the next level and think differently about how they overcome their problems. This is the distillation of all the years I spent building businesses. It is the same rubric I use every day as I build Impact Theory. 

If you want to join, click the link in bio. It is time to make it happen!

node.text:
Here's my best relationship advice - elevate your partner. You've got to want them to win. Relationships require a lot of sacrifices and unless on balance the relationship gives you far more than it takes, what's the point? Everyone has to be responsible for their own emotions and for their own growth, but having someone that makes you feel better about yourself and encourages you to go for broke is magical. So be sure to take time to celebrate and encourage them. Go way the hell out of your way to sincerely compliment them. Don't bullshit, but hone in on the good stuff. You will see more of whatever you focus on, so focus on the good stuff and say it out loud so the other person knows how you feel. 

To that end, I want to shout out my wife @lisabilyeu! Today is her birthday. Baby, I hope this day is awesome for you and you know how much you inspire me. You are an HCMF to be sure and I couldn't be more proud of you. Happy Birthday!!

📸 @Peter_Hurley

node.text:
One thing @lisabilyeu and I have learned is that communication is everything. It is literally going to determine the success or failure of your relationship. You have to define terms, develop keen self awareness, understand each other’s weaknesses, admit your insecurities, and much, much more. And above all of that, is getting good at the hard conversations. First of all, you have to be willing to say the truth, even when it’s the last thing you want to say. The reason is simple, without trust there is no real connection. Over time you will become isolated and resentful. The only way to avoid that fate is to tell the truth even when it means pissing off the other person. I can’t tell you the number of times I’ve been tempted to lie to Lisa because it would spare her feelings or end an argument. But I never do it because I don’t want to lose her trust. In the short term, lying is effective. But in the long term, it destroys. That’s why you’ve got to get good at the hard conversations. 

If you want to hear more depth on topics like this then go subscribe to our relationship channel on YouTube - Relationship Theory. Link in bio.

node.text:
Life can’t be all pleasure or all pain. Without pleasure what reason is there to live? Without pain what stimulus do you have to strive for pleasure?

We often make the false assumption that pain is bad. That pain is to be avoided. In reality pain is just a learning stimulus. In strength training, good pain is a sign you are taxing your body so it will grow stronger. In relationship, pain teaches us what we want out of a partner. In business, pain teaches us to overcome. The pleasure is found in overcoming the pain. In feeling stronger in our skin. In developing a healthy relationship. In seeing your business grow.

Embrace the duality of pain and pleasure and harness them BOTH to maximize your growth.

node.text:
Obsession. That’s the right word. ⁣
⁣
It’s hard to cultivate, but man, it works. ⁣
⁣
When something has a grip on your mind, body, and soul, you put in the work. ⁣
⁣
Long past the point of reason, or even safety, the obsessed go for fucking broke. ⁣
⁣
They leave it all out on the field in the name of greatness. ⁣
⁣
People have such love for natural talent, but give me hard-ass, obsessed work ethic any day. ⁣
⁣
That will beat talent every single fucking time. ⁣
⁣
No one, not even the naturally gifted, become the GOAT without the kind of blinding obsession it takes to dominate. ⁣
⁣
It’s a simple question - do you want to win badly enough that you will pay any price? ⁣
⁣
If not, fair enough. But if you want to be remembered, it’s the only way.

🖊 @behaviorhack

node.text:
The people that surround you will shape you. So be very careful who you draw into your circle. 

When I met @lisabilyeu I did not plan to get married. But there was something about her. I wasn’t just attracted to her, she made me feel better about myself and pushed me to reach for more. So even though everyone thought that we were making a huge mistake - because we were so young (she was only 22 and I was just 26), and we’d only been together for 8 or 9 months when I proposed - we both believed this could work. Even back then we knew it would take work, we knew we wanted to improve, and we believed that together we’d become a lot more than we would by ourselves. So we ignored all of the nay sayers and committed ourselves to the relationship. And I can say now beyond a shadow of a doubt that that was the single best decision I’ve ever made in my life. We have continued to shape and improve each other and I can honestly say I would not be the same person without her. So, if you’ve found the one, don’t be afraid to defy the odds. Just be prepared to put in the work, push each other, and grow together. 

And Baby, to you I say, Happy Anniversary!!! Thank you for pushing me and making my life something I love more than I ever could have imagined. I Love you beyond all reason and measure.
